# User Applications
This system allows loading any web app into the game, the web app is then fed various information automatically from the game client.
The web app is shown directly in the game window, and can be interacted with by the player directly within the game.

See the example app at https://cdn.tycoon.community/dev/userapp/sample.html. It contains the basic code to listen to incoming data and send requests back to the game client.

You can also load the applications `monitor.html` or `application.html` in-game to see all data values in real time.

# Interface
By default, the F1 key opens the User Applications interface. 
The user is requested to input a Web URL for the web app they want to load.

The F1 key is used to regain focus to the web app and display the web app if it was hidden previously.

You can load more than one application at once, by clicking "New Tab" you create an additional application slot. You may currently have up to 5 applications loaded at once.

Tabs are not hidden by default, and will all stay visible at the same time. Apps may have specific behavior based on if they are the active tab or not. You are unable to physically interact with anything not in the current tab.

Pro tip: When you open the interface, but before interacting with anything, you may use the `TAB` key to switch between tabs.

Pro tip: When you open the interface, but before interacting with anything, you may use the `ESC` key to return control to the game (pin the applications).


# Commands
You can send commands to the game from your web app.

The command is sent as a JSON object with `type` set to the command name, and each argument as their own properties.
Eg `{type: "setWaypoint", x: 500, y: 250}`

| Command | Parameters | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
setWaypoint | x : number, y : number | Sets the in-game waypoint
sendCommand | command : string | Sends a console command to the game client
notification | text : string | Shows a notification over the map
info | text : string, time : number | Shows a lingering info message on the bottom right, time is in seconds
getData | No arguments | Forces the game client to send the entire data cache
getNamedData | keys : array | Requests only the named data keys from the cache
close | No arguments | Gives focus back to the game and hides the web app
pin | No arguments | Gives focus back to the game, but keeps the web app on screen
sfx | sfx : number | Plays a SFX, see list below for sfx indexes
popup | title : string, text : string | Shows a full-screen text message
oneliner | text : string | Shows a black mid-screen box with text
message | text : string | Shows a mid-screen text message
shareLocalData | key : string, value : string | Adds a shared key/value pair accessible by all loaded applications (see below)
shareServerData | key : string, value : string | Adds a server-shared key/value pair that is shared with all players (see below)
addBlip | id : string, x : number, y : number | Creates a map blip, given id is used to configure and delete it
removeBlip | id : string | Deletes the given map blip
setBlipPosition | id : string, x : number, y : number | Updates the position of the given map blip
setBlipSprite | id : string, sprite : number | Sets the sprite icon for the map blip, see the FiveM docs for sprite numbers
setBlipColour | id : string, color : number | Sets the sprite color for the map blip, see the FiveM docs for blip colors
setBlipAsShortRange | id : string, alwaysVisible : boolean | Sets the map blip to always be on the radar or not
setBlipRoute | id : string, route : boolean | Enables the GPS to show a route towards the map blip
showTickOnBlip | id : string, ticked : boolean | Places a checkmark overlay on the map blip
showNumberOnBlip | id :string, number : number | Puts a number as text in the center of the map blip
setBlipName | id : string, name : string | Gives the map blip a custom name shown in the legend
buildBlip | id : string, x : number, y : number, sprite : number, color : number, alwaysVisible : boolean, route : boolean, ticked : boolean, name : string | A shortcut command to build a blip in one fell swoop.
registerTrigger | trigger : string, name : string | Registers a bindable key for the specified trigger in the FiveM Keybinds menu
setDivCss | div : string, css : string | Sets the CSS style for a vRP named div. Example names: money, bmoney, job, mission, additional_css.
setDivContent | div : string, content : string | Sets the contents of a named vRP div.
forceMenuChoice | choice : string, mod : number | Forces the given menu choice to be submitted. Mod is -1 for left arrow, 0 for enter and 1 for right arrow.
forceMenuBack | No arguments | Forces the menu to close, or go back. Emulating the cancel button.
forceSubmitValue | value : string | Force submits the given text for the text/number input prompt.
forceRequestResult | result : boolean | Force accepts the first request prompt (F5/F6)
openMainMenu | No arguments | Opens the main menu (M menu) 
interactButton | No arguments | Unused
